termination.standard: {  "terminationClause": {    "title": "Termination",    "sections": [      {        "heading": "Term",        "content": "This Agreement shall commence on the Effective Date and shall continue in full force and effect for a period of [Number] ([Number]) year(s) (the \"Initial Term\"), unless earlier terminated in accordance with the provisions of this Agreement. This Agreement shall automatically renew for successive periods of [Number] ([Number]) year(s) (each a \"Renewal Term\", and collectively with the Initial Term, the \"Term\") unless either party provides written notice of its intent not to renew to the other party at least [Number] ([Number]) days prior to the expiration of the then-current Term."      },      {        "heading": "Termination for Cause",        "content": "Either party may terminate this Agreement immediately upon written notice to the other party if the other party: (a) materially breaches any provision of this Agreement and fails to cure such breach within [Number] ([Number]) days after receiving written notice thereof; (b) becomes insolvent, files a petition for bankruptcy, makes an assignment for the benefit of creditors, or has a receiver or trustee appointed for its assets; or (c) ceases to conduct business in the ordinary course."      },      {        "heading": "Termination for Convenience",        "content": "Either party may terminate this Agreement for any reason or no reason upon providing [Number] ([Number]) days' prior written notice to the other party. In the event of termination for convenience by [Specify Party, e.g., 'Client'], [Specify Consequences, e.g., 'Client shall pay MSP for all services rendered up to the effective date of termination and any non-cancellable expenses incurred by MSP in connection with the services.']."      },      {        "heading": "Effect of Termination",        "content": "Upon the expiration or termination of this Agreement for any reason: (a) all rights and obligations of the parties shall cease, except for those provisions that are intended to survive termination, including but not limited to confidentiality, indemnification, and limitation of liability; (b) [Specify Deliverables/Data Handling, e.g., 'Company shall promptly return to MSP all Confidential Information and materials provided by MSP.'] and (c) [Specify Payment Obligations, e.g., 'Client shall pay MSP for all services rendered and expenses incurred prior to the effective date of termination.']"      },      {        "heading": "Survival",        "content": "The provisions of Sections [List Sections, e.g., 'Confidentiality', 'Indemnification', 'Limitation of Liability', 'Governing Law', and 'Dispute Resolution'] shall survive the expiration or termination of this Agreement."      }    ],    "notes": "This is a comprehensive termination clause template. Specific details like notice periods, cure periods, and consequences of termination should be carefully reviewed and adjusted based on the specific nature of the services and the relationship between QDB and the other party."  }}

payment_terms.standard: {  "paymentTerms": {    "title": "Payment Terms",    "description": "The following outlines the standard payment terms for services rendered by QDB company.",    "sections": [      {        "heading": "Invoicing",        "content": "Invoices shall be submitted by QDB company to the client on a [monthly/quarterly/project milestone] basis. All invoices will be due and payable within [30] days of the invoice date. Invoices shall be sent electronically to the billing contact designated by the client."      },      {        "heading": "Payment Methods",        "content": "QDB company accepts payment via [electronic funds transfer (EFT), check, or other agreed-upon method]. Details for EFT payments will be provided on the invoice. Checks should be made payable to 'QDB company' and mailed to [QDB company's mailing address]."      },      {        "heading": "Late Payments",        "content": "Payments not received within [30] days of the invoice date may be subject to a late payment fee of [1.5]% per month or the maximum rate permitted by law, whichever is less. QDB company reserves the right to suspend services if payments become [60] days or more past due."      },      {        "heading": "Expenses",        "content": "Unless otherwise specified in a separate agreement, all reasonable out-of-pocket expenses incurred by QDB company in connection with the services provided (e.g., travel, accommodation, materials) shall be reimbursed by the client upon submission of itemized receipts. Such expenses will be included on the regular invoice."      },      {        "heading": "Taxes",        "content": "All fees and charges set forth herein are exclusive of any sales, use, excise, value-added or similar taxes. Client shall be responsible for the payment of all such taxes applicable to the services provided, except for taxes based on QDB company's net income."      }    ],    "notes": "These payment terms may be modified by a separate written agreement between QDB company and the client."  }}

indemnification.standard: {  "indemnification_clause": {    "title": "Indemnification",    "sections": [      {        "heading": "Indemnification by Company",        "content": "The Company shall indemnify, defend, and hold harmless the Indemnified Parties from and against any and all claims, liabilities, losses, damages, costs, and expenses (including reasonable attorneys’ fees and costs) arising out of or relating to (a) any breach by the Company of any of its representations, warranties, covenants, or obligations under this Agreement; (b) any gross negligence or willful misconduct of the Company in connection with the performance of its obligations hereunder; or (c) any infringement or alleged infringement by the Company's products or services (as provided to the Indemnified Parties) of any intellectual property rights of any third party; provided, however, that the Company shall have no obligation to indemnify, defend, or hold harmless the Indemnified Parties to the extent any such claim, liability, loss, damage, cost, or expense arises from the gross negligence or willful misconduct of the Indemnified Parties, or their respective officers, directors, employees, or agents."      },      {        "heading": "Indemnification by Service Provider",        "content": "The Service Provider shall indemnify, defend, and hold harmless the Indemnified Parties from and against any and all claims, liabilities, losses, damages, costs, and expenses (including reasonable attorneys’ fees and costs) arising out of or relating to (a) any breach by the Service Provider of any of its representations, warranties, covenants, or obligations under this Agreement; (b) any gross negligence or willful misconduct of the Service Provider in connection with the performance of its obligations hereunder; (c) any infringement or alleged infringement by the Service Provider's products or services (as provided to the Company) of any intellectual property rights of any third party; (d) any injury to or death of any person, or damage to or destruction of any tangible property, caused by the acts or omissions of the Service Provider, its employees, agents, or subcontractors; or (e) any violation by the Service Provider of any applicable laws or regulations; provided, however, that the Service Provider shall have no obligation to indemnify, defend, or hold harmless the Indemnified Parties to the extent any such claim, liability, loss, damage, cost, or expense arises from the gross negligence or willful misconduct of the Indemnified Parties, or their respective officers, directors, employees, or agents."      },      {        "heading": "Indemnification Procedures",        "content": "In the event that a party (the “Indemnifying Party”) is obligated to indemnify, defend, and hold harmless the other party (the “Indemnified Party”) under this Section, the Indemnified Party shall provide the Indemnifying Party with prompt written notice of any claim, action, suit, or proceeding for which indemnification is sought. The Indemnified Party shall cooperate with the Indemnifying Party, at the Indemnifying Party’s expense, in the defense of any such claim. The Indemnifying Party shall have the right to control the defense of any such claim, including the right to select counsel and to settle any such claim, provided that the Indemnifying Party shall not settle any claim in a manner that admits fault on behalf of the Indemnified Party or imposes any obligations on the Indemnified Party without the Indemnified Party’s prior written consent, which consent shall not be unreasonably withheld or delayed."      },      {        "heading": "Third-Party Beneficiaries",        "content": "The provisions of this Section are for the benefit of the Indemnified Parties and their respective officers, directors, employees, agents, successors, and assigns, and each of them shall have the right to enforce the provisions of this Section directly against the Indemnifying Party. This Section shall survive the termination or expiration of this Agreement."      }    ],    "definitions": {      "indemnified_parties": "The Company, its Affiliates, and their respective officers, directors, employees, agents, successors, and assigns.",      "company": "QDB Company or its designated affiliate.",      "service_provider": "The counterparty providing services or goods under this Agreement.",      "affiliates": "With respect to any entity, any other entity that directly or indirectly controls, is controlled by, or is under common control with such entity. For purposes of this definition, 'control' means the possession, directly or indirectly, of the power to direct or cause the direction of the management and policies of such entity, whether through the ownership of voting securities, by contract, or otherwise."    }  }}

confidentiality.standard: {  "confidentiality_clause": {    "title": "Confidentiality",    "sections": [      {        "heading": "Definition of Confidential Information",        "content": "For the purposes of this Agreement, \"Confidential Information\" shall mean any and all information, in whatever form or medium, disclosed by one party (the \"Disclosing Party\") to the other party (the \"Receiving Party\") that is proprietary or confidential, or that the Disclosing Party reasonably believes to be proprietary or confidential. Confidential Information includes, but is not limited to, trade secrets, business plans, financial information, customer lists, technical data, software, source code, object code, algorithms, designs, specifications, marketing strategies, and any other information relating to the Disclosing Party's business, operations, products, or services. Confidential Information shall not include information that (a) is or becomes publicly known or available without breach of this Agreement by the Receiving Party; (b) was rightfully known to the Receiving Party prior to its disclosure by the Disclosing Party, free of any obligation of confidence; (c) is rightfully obtained by the Receiving Party from a third party without breach of any obligation of confidence; or (d) is independently developed by the Receiving Party without use of or reference to the Disclosing Party's Confidential Information."      },      {        "heading": "Obligations of Receiving Party",        "content": "The Receiving Party agrees to hold the Disclosing Party's Confidential Information in strict confidence and to take all reasonable precautions to protect such Confidential Information. The Receiving Party shall not, without the prior written consent of the Disclosing Party, disclose any Confidential Information to any third party, or use such Confidential Information for any purpose other than to perform its obligations or exercise its rights under this Agreement."      },      {        "heading": "Permitted Disclosures",        "content": "Notwithstanding the foregoing, the Receiving Party may disclose Confidential Information to its employees, agents, and subcontractors who have a \"need to know\" such information for the purpose of this Agreement, provided that such individuals are bound by confidentiality obligations no less restrictive than those contained herein. The Receiving Party shall be responsible for any breach of confidentiality by its employees, agents, or subcontractors."      },      {        "heading": "Return or Destruction of Confidential Information",        "content": "Upon the Disclosing Party's written request, or upon termination or expiration of this Agreement, the Receiving Party shall promptly return to the Disclosing Party all Confidential Information in its possession or control, or, at the Disclosing Party's option, destroy all such Confidential Information and provide written certification of such destruction. Notwithstanding the foregoing, the Receiving Party may retain one copy of the Disclosing Party's Confidential Information solely for archival purposes and to comply with legal or regulatory requirements, provided that such retained information remains subject to the confidentiality obligations set forth in this Agreement."      },      {        "heading": "Term of Confidentiality",        "content": "The obligations of confidentiality set forth in this Section shall survive the termination or expiration of this Agreement for a period of [Insert Duration, e.g., five (5) years]."      },      {        "heading": "Remedies",        "content": "The Receiving Party acknowledges that any breach of its confidentiality obligations may cause irreparable harm to the Disclosing Party for which monetary damages alone would not be an adequate remedy. Accordingly, in the event of a breach or threatened breach of this Section, the Disclosing Party shall be entitled to seek injunctive relief, in addition to any other remedies available at law or in equity."      }    ]  }}

intellectual_property.standard: {  "intellectualPropertyClause": {    "title": "Ownership of Intellectual Property",    "sections": [      {        "heading": "Background Intellectual Property",        "content": "All intellectual property rights, including but not limited to copyrights, patents, trademarks, trade secrets, and any other proprietary rights, existing prior to the execution of this Agreement or developed by a party independently of this Agreement, shall remain the sole and exclusive property of that party (the \"Background IP\"). Each party hereby grants to the other party a non-exclusive, non-transferable, royalty-free license to use its Background IP solely to the extent necessary for the other party to perform its obligations or exercise its rights under this Agreement."      },      {        "heading": "Developed Intellectual Property",        "content": "All intellectual property rights in any materials, software, documentation, inventions, discoveries, designs, works of authorship, and any other deliverables created or developed by QDB Company (or its employees, contractors, or agents) in the course of providing services or performing obligations under this Agreement (the \"Developed IP\") shall be and remain the sole and exclusive property of QDB Company. Notwithstanding the foregoing, if the parties agree in writing that specific deliverables are to be transferred to the other party, QDB Company shall grant to such party a perpetual, non-exclusive, non-transferable, royalty-free license to use the Developed IP incorporated within such deliverables solely for the purpose of operating and utilizing the delivered products or services.  The other party shall not acquire any ownership rights in the Developed IP, nor shall it have the right to modify, adapt, reverse engineer, decompile, or disassemble any aspect of the Developed IP beyond its intended use within the delivered products or services."      },      {        "heading": "Third-Party Materials",        "content": "In the event that the performance of this Agreement requires the use of any third-party intellectual property (the \"Third-Party Materials\"), QDB Company shall use commercially reasonable efforts to obtain the necessary licenses or rights for the use of such Third-Party Materials. The terms and conditions of such licenses shall be incorporated herein by reference, and the other party agrees to comply with all such terms and conditions. QDB Company shall not be responsible for any breach of third-party license terms by the other party."      },      {        "heading": "Confidentiality of Intellectual Property",        "content": "Both parties acknowledge that the Background IP and Developed IP may contain confidential and proprietary information. Each party agrees to maintain the confidentiality of such information and to use it only for the purposes set forth in this Agreement, in accordance with the confidentiality provisions of this Agreement."      },      {        "heading": "No Implied Licenses",        "content": "Nothing in this Agreement shall be construed as granting any implied license or right to use any intellectual property of QDB Company, except as expressly provided herein."      }    ]  }}

warranties.standard: {  "clauseTitle": "Standard Warranties",  "version": "1.0",  "effectiveDate": "As of the Effective Date",  "providerName": "QDB Company",  "clientName": "[Client Name]",  "clauseText": [    {      "paragraphNumber": "Warranties",      "content": "QDB Company warrants that the Services provided under this Agreement will be performed in a professional and workmanlike manner, consistent with industry standards and in accordance with the specifications outlined in any applicable Statement of Work. dispute_resolution.standard: {  "disputeResolution": {    "title": "Dispute Resolution",    "description": "This clause outlines the procedures for resolving any disputes that may arise between the parties under this Agreement, aiming for an efficient and fair resolution process.",    "sections": [      {        "title": "Informal Negotiation",        "content": "The parties agree to attempt to resolve any dispute, controversy, or claim arising out of or relating to this Agreement, or the breach, termination, or invalidity thereof, in the first instance through good faith negotiation. Senior management representatives of each party, with authority to settle the dispute, shall meet within fifteen (15) calendar days of the written request of a party to the other party. Such representatives shall meet at such mutually agreed location and time as they deem appropriate and shall continue, in good faith, to attempt to reach a mutually acceptable resolution of the dispute."      },      {        "title": "Mediation",        "content": "If the dispute cannot be resolved through informal negotiation within thirty (30) calendar days of the initial request for negotiation, the parties agree to attempt to resolve the dispute through mediation administered by a mutually agreed-upon mediation service. The mediator shall be selected by the parties. The mediation shall take place in San Antonio, Texas, or such other location as the parties may agree. The costs of mediation shall be borne equally by the parties. The parties agree to participate in the mediation in good faith and to be bound by any settlement agreement reached."      },      {        "title": "Arbitration",        "content": "If the dispute cannot be resolved through mediation, the parties agree that any unresolved dispute, controversy, or claim arising out of or relating to this Agreement, or the breach, termination, or invalidity thereof, shall be settled by binding arbitration administered by the American Arbitration Association (AAA) under its Commercial Arbitration Rules. The arbitration shall be conducted in San Antonio, Texas. The arbitration shall be conducted by a single arbitrator mutually agreed upon by the parties, or if the parties cannot agree, by an arbitrator appointed by the AAA. The arbitrator's decision shall be final and binding on the parties, and judgment on the award rendered by the arbitrator may be entered in any court having jurisdiction thereof. Each party shall bear its own costs and expenses in connection with the arbitration, and the parties shall share equally the fees and expenses of the arbitrator."      },      {        "title": "Governing Law",        "content": "This Agreement and all matters arising out of or relating to this Agreement shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of the State of Texas, without regard to its conflict of laws principles."      },      {        "title": "Jurisdiction",        "content": "The parties irrevocably consent and submit to the exclusive jurisdiction of the state and federal courts located in Bexar County, Texas, for the purpose of resolving any disputes arising under or related to this Agreement that are not resolved through arbitration as provided herein."      }    ]  }}
